{"type":"message","id":"f3c18849","parentId":"01bb7bd0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:10:51.853Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_qcus3v7bm3t7_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5744\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/TIC-SPEC.md' new_len=1248\n[mutation proposed] research/TIC-SPEC.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 021015 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires analyzing pulse logs to find invariant vs variant patterns. I need to first understand the structure of existing logs and then implement the classifier.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"warm-summit","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5744\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/TIC-SPEC.md' new_len=1248\n[mutation proposed] research/TIC-SPEC.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 021015 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires analyzing pulse logs to find invariant vs variant patterns. I need to first understand the structure of existing logs and then implement the classifier.\n","name":"powershell Bypass"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774332651851}}
